    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-02-15T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-02-15T13:00:00-05:00" n="565"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d565">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.4121/283: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-02-15T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 15, 1936—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>55. Your despatch No. 1933, January 27. Draft Convention approved. Advise whether
                    full powers will be forwarded soon so convention can be sent to Senate during
                    present session.</p>
                <p>Inquire whether Foreign Office agrees with the Department that notices of
                    adherence given by the two Governments under the Convention of 1899 as
                    supplemented by the Convention of 1902<note n="84" xml:id="d565fn84">Signed
                        January 13, 1902, <ref target="frus1916#pg_289">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1916, p. 289</ref>.</note>
                    will remain unaffected by the coming into operation of the present
                    Convention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
